{"expand":"renderedFields,names,schema,transitions,operations,editmeta,changelog","id":"145578","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/latest/issue/145578","key":"PLXCOMP-220","fields":{"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"summary":"[REGRESSION] Tar archiver produces tar files with invalid uid/gid fields on Windows","timetracking":{},"issuetype":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png","name":"Bug","subtask":false},"customfield_10110":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/customFieldOption/10040","value":"yes","id":"10040"},"votes":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/PLXCOMP-220/votes","votes":0,"hasVoted":false},"resolution":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/resolution/1","id":"1","description":"A fix for this issue is checked into the tree and tested.","name":"Fixed"},"fixVersions":[{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/version/18922","id":"18922","name":"plexus-io-2.0.7","archived":false,"released":true,"releaseDate":"2013-04-18"},{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/version/19189","id":"19189","name":"plexus-archiver-2.4.1","archived":false,"released":true,"releaseDate":"2013-04-19"}],"resolutiondate":"2013-04-23T14:18:30.957-0500","customfield_10210":"0.0","timespent":null,"reporter":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=sergei_ivanov","name":"sergei_ivanov","emailAddress":"sergei_ivanov@mail.ru","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312"},"displayName":"Sergei Ivanov","active":true},"aggregatetimeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_10161":["krosenvold(krosenvold)","sergei_ivanov(sergei_ivanov)"],"customfield_10160":null,"updated":"2013-04-23T17:06:06.009-0500","created":"2013-04-15T18:57:17.027-0500","description":"The latest plexus-archiver does not populate uid/gid entries in a tar file, when that tar file is being created on Windows, which causes compatibility problems with some tools (python/jython is one known victim). Previous versions of plexus-archiver used to populate uid/gid with {{0}} on Windows.\r\n\r\nThe changes that introduced this regression were PLXCOMP-200 and PLXCOMP-201. An NPE was fixed in PLXCOMP-200 and plexus-io-2.0.3, then integrated into plexus-archiver-2.1.1. A change in PLXCOMP-201 fixed another problem and became part of plexus-io-2.0.4 and plexus-archiver-2.1.2. It appears that an additional change is required to put these components in order.\r\n\r\nThis is a compound problem that spans both plexus-archiver and plexus-io. In brief, there is no uid/gid information available on Windows, which causes plexus components to use defaults. The problem arises from the fact that plexus-io classes ({{PlexusIoFileResourceCollection}} and the likes) use {{-1}} or {{null}} as a default value for uid/gid, whereas {{TarArchiver}} and {{TarEntry}} from plexus-archiver use {{0}} as the default value. After the recent changes in plexus-io, {{TarArchiver}} ended up passing {{-1}} down to {{TarEntry}}, which is not correctly handled when encoded into the output stream.\r\n\r\nI have got a patch ready that I shall submit as a pull request. The full list of changes is as follows:\r\n# {{org.codehaus.plexus.components.io.attributes.PlexusIoResourceAttributeUtils#mergeAttributes()}}\r\nshould not apply default uid/gid if they are either {{null}} or negative\r\n# {{org.codehaus.plexus.archiver.tar.TarArchiver#tarFile()}}\r\nshould check for negative values when populating uid/gid in {{TarEntry}}\r\n# {{org.codehaus.plexus.archiver.tar.TarEntry#writeEntryHeader()}}\r\nshould check for negative uid/gid and write out {{0}} instead\r\n","priority":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/priority/1","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/priorities/blocker.png","name":"Blocker","id":"1"},"duedate":null,"issuelinks":[{"id":"32879","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issueLink/32879","type":{"id":"10010","name":"Related","inward":"is related to","outward":"relates to","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issueLinkType/10010"},"inwardIssue":{"id":"134672","key":"PLXCOMP-201","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/134672","fields":{"summary":"PlexusIoResourceAttributeUtils - GroupId may not be set on partial overrides","status":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/statuses/closed.png","name":"Closed","id":"6"},"priority":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/priorities/major.png","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png","name":"Bug","subtask":false}}}}],"customfield_10163":"54518400","watches":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/PLXCOMP-220/watchers","watchCount":2,"isWatching":false},"worklog":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":20,"total":0,"worklogs":[]},"subtasks":[],"status":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/statuses/closed.png","name":"Closed","id":"6"},"customfield_10090":null,"labels":[]