me":"Sergei Ivanov","active":true},"created":"2013-04-17T19:51:19.431-0500","updated":"2013-04-17T19:51:19.431-0500"},{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/145578/comment/323865","id":"323865","author":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=krosenvold","name":"krosenvold","emailAddress":"krosenvold@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127"},"displayName":"Kristian Rosenvold","active":true},"body":"Revised patch looks good. The plexus-io code is the kind of code that's really cool when you write it (the first time) but everyone hates you for later; too many layers of abstraction and way too much leaky abstractions that need later workarounds. And the workarounds need subsequent workarounds.\r\n\r\nSome beautiful day (when we have 28 hours to the day, most likely) I would like to rewrite the whole thing.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, thanks for an excellent patch that seems to work well. I will apply it to master later tonight\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=krosenvold","name":"krosenvold","emailAddress":"krosenvold@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127"},"displayName":"Kristian Rosenvold","active":true},"created":"2013-04-18T01:34:14.300-0500","updated":"2013-04-18T01:34:14.300-0500"},{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/145578/comment/323917","id":"323917","author":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=sergei_ivanov","name":"sergei_ivanov","emailAddress":"sergei_ivanov@mail.ru","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312"},"displayName":"Sergei Ivanov","active":true},"body":"Thank you for reviewing and applying the changes. I do hope that this time no downstream projects will be broken. As soon as the new versions of artifacts are in maven central, we shall test them inside our in-house packaging plugin for maven, which caused all the trouble in the first place and made Alex submit the ill-fated initial patches.\r\n\r\nPlease note however, that there are two outstanding unmerged pull requests on the PLXCOMP-220 branch for plexus-archiver, which did not make it into 2.4.\r\n\r\nFor housekeeping purposes, pull requests for plexus-io (both successfully merged into p-io-2.0.7):\r\n# https://github.com/sonatype/plexus-io/pull/2\r\n# https://github.com/sonatype/plexus-io/pull/3\r\n\r\nPull requests for plexus-archiver (still outstanding):\r\n# https://github.com/sonatype/plexus-archiver/pull/7\r\n# https://github.com/sonatype/plexus-archiver/pull/8\r\n\r\nCan you please mark PLXCOMP-201 as resolved (please see my comments at the bottom of it), and link all three issues in Jira as follows:\r\n* PLXCOMP-220 \"caused by\" PLXCOMP-201\r\n* PLXCOMP-201 \"caused by\" PLXCOMP-200\r\n\r\nThank you again for taking your time spent in reviewing, testing and merging the changes.","updateAuthor":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=sergei_ivanov","name":"sergei_ivanov","emailAddress":"sergei_ivanov@mail.ru","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?ownerId=sergei_ivanov&avatarId=11312"},"displayName":"Sergei Ivanov","active":true},"created":"2013-04-18T18:17:59.443-0500","updated":"2013-04-18T18:17:59.443-0500"},{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/145578/comment/323923","id":"323923","author":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=krosenvold","name":"krosenvold","emailAddress":"krosenvold@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","32x32":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","48x48":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127"},"displayName":"Kristian Rosenvold","active":true},"body":"Ah! I seem to have made a mess of the archiver 2.4 release; I tested all your changes but obviously forgot to push them. So none of your changes to archiver are actually in 2.4.\r\n\r\nI tested a fair amount of downstream projects with their IT's too, so I do believe we're in a better shape now than ever, thanks to your thorough work.\r\n\r\nI will publish a 2.4.1 this afternoon with your changes.\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/user?username=krosenvold","name":"krosenvold","emailAddress":"krosenvold@apache.org","avatarUrls":{"16x16":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=krosenvold&avatarId=11127","24x24":"http://jira.codehaus.org/secure/u